            "answer_text": "Wikipedia actually has a great page on this that\u2019s very well-researched. There\u2019s a chart with everything listed out, but it can be a little hard to read. Here\u2019s a summary of the most efficient ways to travel, with all the numbers converted into fuel consumption figures: Velomobile (4470 MPG, 0.053 L/100km)Electric Scooter (2000 MPG, 0.118 L/100km)Bicycle (732 MPG, 0.32 L/100km)Motorized Bicycle (670 MPG, 0.35 L/100km)Walking (360 MPG, 0.65 L/100km)Urban Rail (186 MPG, 1.26 L/100km)Electric Car (145 MPG, 1.62 L/100km)Bus (66.5 MPG, 3.53 L/100km)So a bicycle isn\u2019t quite the most efficient form of transportation - an aerodynamic velomobile is a good bit better:  Followed by one of those electric scooters, which are kind-of the new kid on the block for transportation:  In fact, both of these are multiple times more efficient than just bicycling around. ",
