            "answer_text": "yes, as long as you include the invention of roads in the calculations. Bicycles without roads are less efficient than walking. On the other hand, if you accrue the cost of building roads onto the cost of travelling by bicycle, their efficiency vanishes. So, the answer is: yes, bicycles are the most efficient form of human transportation ever invented, as long as, casually, there is a road that connects the point of departure with the point of arrival, and the cost of building the road has been already accounted for. Outside of this very strict condition, this is the most efficient form of human transporation:  ",
